<SiteLayout title="Saachi K Gupta" showHero={true}>
  <div style="max-width: 60ch; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.6; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem;">
    <p style="margin: 0;">I'm a product and finance leader at Amazon — connecting product, finance, and operations to turn messy data into clear decisions that move billions of dollars and hundreds of stakeholders.</p>
    <p style="margin: 0;">I'm as comfortable in SQL and Python as I am influencing VPs and engineers to align on a shared narrative.</p>
    <p style="margin: 0;">I hold an MBA from Wharton, where I focused on Operations and Entrepreneurship, and a BA in Economics and Political Science from the University of Chicago.</p>
    <p style="margin: 0;">Building community matters to me too — through SheJumps, Amazon's finance rotational programs, and student organizations I led at Wharton and UChicago.</p>
    <p style="margin: 0;">Outside of work, you'll find me backpacking, training for triathlons, scuba diving, or working on craft projects.</p>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
